name: ADAS_ACTIVE_AUTONOMY_LEVEL
comment: Complies with https://www.sae.org/standards/content/j3016_202104/ and https://www.sae.org/blog/sae-j3016-update. Level 5 and 4 ADS (Automated driving system) disengage, if appropriate, only after it achieves a minimal risk condition or a driver is performing the DDT. Level 3 ADS disengages either an appropriate time after issuing a request to intervene or immediately upon user request. Level 2 DAS (Driving automation system) disengages immediately upon driver request. However, since many Level 2 DAS, often termed "Level 2.5", warn the driver shortly before reaching their operational limits, the VSS also supports the DISENGAGING state for SAE_2. Nevertheless, it should be noted that the SAE J3016 states that it is incorrect to describe driving automation features using fractional levels.
configString: Indicates the currently active level of driving automation according to the SAE J3016 (Taxonomy and Definitions for Terms Related to Driving Automation Systems for On-Road Motor Vehicles).

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_INTENSITY
configString: Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_IS_WIPERS_WORN
configString: Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_MODE
configString: Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_ACTUAL_POSITION
comment: Default parking position might be used as reference position.
configString: Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_DRIVE_CURRENT
comment: May be negative in special situations.
configString: Actual current used by wiper drive.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_FREQUENCY
comment: Examples - 0 = Wipers stopped, 80 = Wipers doing 80 cycles per minute (in WIPE mode).
configString: Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_BLOCKED
configString: Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_ENDING_WIPE_CYCLE
comment: In continuous wiping between A and B this sensor can be used a trigger to update TargetPosition.
configString: Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_OVERHEATED
configString: Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_POSITION_REACHED
configString: Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_WIPER_ERROR
configString: Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_WIPING
configString: Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_MODE
configString: Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_SYSTEM_TARGET_POSITION
comment: Default parking position might be used as reference position.
configString: Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_FRONT_WIPING_WIPER_WEAR
configString: Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_INTENSITY
configString: Relative intensity/sensitivity for interval and rain sensor mode as requested by user/driver. Has no significance if Windshield.Wiping.Mode is OFF/SLOW/MEDIUM/FAST 0 - wipers inactive. 1 - minimum intensity (lowest frequency/sensitivity, longest interval). 2/3/4/... - higher intensity (higher frequency/sensitivity, shorter interval). Maximum value supported is vehicle specific.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_IS_WIPERS_WORN
configString: Wiper wear status. True = Worn, Replacement recommended or required. False = Not Worn.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_MODE
configString: Wiper mode requested by user/driver. INTERVAL indicates intermittent wiping, with fixed time interval between each wipe. RAIN_SENSOR indicates intermittent wiping based on rain intensity.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_ACTUAL_POSITION
comment: Default parking position might be used as reference position.
configString: Actual position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_DRIVE_CURRENT
comment: May be negative in special situations.
configString: Actual current used by wiper drive.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_FREQUENCY
comment: Examples - 0 = Wipers stopped, 80 = Wipers doing 80 cycles per minute (in WIPE mode).
configString: Wiping frequency/speed, measured in cycles per minute. The signal concerns the actual speed of the wiper blades when moving. Intervals/pauses are excluded, i.e. the value corresponds to the number of cycles that would be completed in 1 minute if wiping permanently over default range.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_BLOCKED
configString: Indicates if wiper movement is blocked. True = Movement blocked. False = Movement not blocked.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_ENDING_WIPE_CYCLE
comment: In continuous wiping between A and B this sensor can be used a trigger to update TargetPosition.
configString: Indicates if current wipe movement is completed or near completion. True = Movement is completed or near completion. Changes to RequestedPosition will be executed first after reaching previous RequestedPosition, if it has not already been reached. False = Movement is not near completion. Any change to RequestedPosition will be executed immediately. Change of direction may not be allowed.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_OVERHEATED
configString: Indicates if wiper system is overheated. True = Wiper system overheated. False = Wiper system not overheated.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_POSITION_REACHED
configString: Indicates if a requested position has been reached. IsPositionReached refers to the previous position in case the TargetPosition is updated while IsEndingWipeCycle=True. True = Current or Previous TargetPosition reached. False = Position not (yet) reached, or wipers have moved away from the reached position.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_WIPER_ERROR
configString: Indicates system failure. True if wiping is disabled due to system failure.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_IS_WIPING
configString: Indicates wiper movement. True if wiper blades are moving. Change of direction shall be considered as IsWiping if wipers will continue to move directly after the change of direction.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_MODE
configString: Requested mode of wiper system. STOP_HOLD means that the wipers shall move to position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position. WIPE means that wipers shall move to the position given by TargetPosition and then hold the position if no new TargetPosition is requested. PLANT_MODE means that wiping is disabled. Exact behavior is vehicle specific. EMERGENCY_STOP means that wiping shall be immediately stopped without holding the position.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_SYSTEM_TARGET_POSITION
comment: Default parking position might be used as reference position.
configString: Requested position of main wiper blade for the wiper system relative to reference position. Location of reference position (0 degrees) and direction of positive/negative degrees is vehicle specific. System behavior when receiving TargetPosition depends on Mode and IsEndingWipeCycle. Supported values are vehicle specific and might be dynamically corrected. If IsEndingWipeCycle=True then wipers will complete current movement before actuating new TargetPosition. If IsEndingWipeCycle=False then wipers will directly change destination if the TargetPosition is changed.

name: BODY_WINDSHIELD_REAR_WIPING_WIPER_WEAR
configString: Wiper wear as percent. 0 = No Wear. 100 = Worn. Replacement required. Method for calculating or estimating wiper wear is vehicle specific. For windshields with multiple wipers the wear reported shall correspond to the most worn wiper.

name: OCCUPANT_ROW1_DRIVER_SIDE_HEAD_POSITION_PITCH
configString: Head pitch angle, measured as angle from vehicle sprung mass XY-plane as defined by ISO 23150:2023 to the head X-axis. 0 = Head in normal position. Positive values = Head leaning up. Negative values = Head leaning down.

name: OCCUPANT_ROW1_DRIVER_SIDE_HEAD_POSITION_ROLL
configString: Head roll angle about the head X-axis (right-hand rule). 0 = Head in normal position. Positive values = Head leaning to the right. Negative values = Head leaning to the left.

name: OCCUPANT_ROW1_DRIVER_SIDE_HEAD_POSITION_X
configString: Longitudinal position of head center measured as mid eye position on X-axis of the vehicle rear-axle coordinate system as defined by ISO 23150:2023 section 3.7.12 Mid eye position refers to the center of a line drawn between the center of the drivers eyes. Positive values = forward of (first) rear-axle. Negative values = backward of (first) rear-axle.

name: OCCUPANT_ROW1_DRIVER_SIDE_HEAD_POSITION_Y
configString: Lateral position of head center measured as mid eye position on X-axis of the vehicle rear-axle coordinate system as defined by ISO 23150:2023 section 3.7.12 Mid eye position refers to the center of a line drawn between the center of the drivers eyes. Positive values = left of rear-axle center. Negative values = right of rear-axle center.

name: OCCUPANT_ROW1_DRIVER_SIDE_HEAD_POSITION_YAW
configString: Head yaw angle, measured from the vehicle sprung mass X-axis as defined by ISO 23150:2023 to the head X-axis, around the vehicle Z-axis (right-hand rule). 0 = Head in normal position. Positive values = Head turned left. Negative values = Head turned right.

name: OCCUPANT_ROW1_DRIVER_SIDE_HEAD_POSITION_Z
configString: Height position of head center measured as mid eye position on X-axis of the vehicle rear-axle coordinate system as defined by ISO 23150:2023 section 3.7.12 Mid eye position refers to the center of a line drawn between the center of the drivers eyes. Positive values = above center of rear-axle reference point. Negative values = below center of rear-axle reference point.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_BATTERY_CONDITIONING_IS_ACTIVE
comment: This signal is typically true when mode is not INACTIVE and time is within defined start/end times.
configString: Indicates if battery conditioning is active (i.e. actively monitors battery temperature). True = Active. False = Inactive.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_BATTERY_CONDITIONING_IS_ONGOING
comment: When battery conditioning is active, but temperature is already within acceptable range so that no cooling or heating is needed then IsOngoing shall report False.
configString: Indicating if battery conditioning is currently ongoing. Battery conditioning is considered ongoing when the battery conditioning system is actively heating or cooling the battery, or requesting heating or cooling.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_BATTERY_CONDITIONING_REQUESTED_MODE
comment: The Mode and TargetTime can be used to calculate TargetTemperature and StartTime

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_BATTERY_CONDITIONING_START_TIME

configString: Start time for battery conditioning, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_BATTERY_CONDITIONING_TARGET_TEMPERATURE

configString: Target temperature for battery conditioning.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_BATTERY_CONDITIONING_TARGET_TIME

configString: Target time when conditioning shall be finished, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_CHARGING_PORT_ANY_POSITION_SUPPORTED_INLET_TYPES
comment: A vehicle may have multiple charging ports. IEC_TYPE_1_AC refers to Type 1 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Yazaki or J1772 connector. IEC_TYPE_2_AC refers to Type 2 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Mennekes connector. IEC_TYPE_3_AC refers to Type 3 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Scame connector. IEC_TYPE_4_DC refers to AA configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as Type 4 or CHAdeMO connector. IEC_TYPE_1_CCS_DC refers to EE Configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as CCS1 or Combo1 connector. IEC_TYPE_2_CCS_DC refers to FF Configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as CCS2 or Combo2 connector. TESLA_ROADSTER, TESLA_HPWC (High Power Wall Connector) and TESLA_SUPERCHARGER refer to non-standardized charging ports/methods used by Tesla. GBT_AC refers to connector specified in GB/T 20234.2. GBT_DC refers to connector specified in GB/T 20234.3. Also specified as BB Configuration in IEC 62196-3. OTHER shall be used for charging ports not included in the list above. For additional information see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEC_62196.
configString: A list of the supported (i.e., available) charging inlets in a particular charging port. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_CHARGING_PORT_REAR_MIDDLE_SUPPORTED_INLET_TYPES
comment: A vehicle may have multiple charging ports. IEC_TYPE_1_AC refers to Type 1 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Yazaki or J1772 connector. IEC_TYPE_2_AC refers to Type 2 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Mennekes connector. IEC_TYPE_3_AC refers to Type 3 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Scame connector. IEC_TYPE_4_DC refers to AA configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as Type 4 or CHAdeMO connector. IEC_TYPE_1_CCS_DC refers to EE Configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as CCS1 or Combo1 connector. IEC_TYPE_2_CCS_DC refers to FF Configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as CCS2 or Combo2 connector. TESLA_ROADSTER, TESLA_HPWC (High Power Wall Connector) and TESLA_SUPERCHARGER refer to non-standardized charging ports/methods used by Tesla. GBT_AC refers to connector specified in GB/T 20234.2. GBT_DC refers to connector specified in GB/T 20234.3. Also specified as BB Configuration in IEC 62196-3. OTHER shall be used for charging ports not included in the list above. For additional information see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEC_62196.
configString: A list of the supported (i.e., available) charging inlets in a particular charging port. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_CHARGING_PORT_REAR_RIGHT_IS_CHARGING_CABLE_CONNECTED
configString: Indicates whether a charging cable is physically connected to a particular charging port or not.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_CHARGING_PORT_REAR_RIGHT_IS_CHARGING_CABLE_LOCKED
comment: Locking of charging cable can be used to prevent unintentional removing during charging.
configString: Is charging cable locked to prevent removal.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_CHARGING_PORT_REAR_RIGHT_IS_FLAP_OPEN
comment: True = at least one flap of this port is open, False = All flaps of this port are closed.
configString: Status of the charging port flap(s).

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_CHARGING_PORT_REAR_RIGHT_SUPPORTED_INLET_TYPES
comment: A vehicle may have multiple charging ports. IEC_TYPE_1_AC refers to Type 1 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Yazaki or J1772 connector. IEC_TYPE_2_AC refers to Type 2 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Mennekes connector. IEC_TYPE_3_AC refers to Type 3 as defined in IEC 62196-2. Also known as Scame connector. IEC_TYPE_4_DC refers to AA configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as Type 4 or CHAdeMO connector. IEC_TYPE_1_CCS_DC refers to EE Configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as CCS1 or Combo1 connector. IEC_TYPE_2_CCS_DC refers to FF Configuration as defined in IEC 62196-3. Also known as CCS2 or Combo2 connector. TESLA_ROADSTER, TESLA_HPWC (High Power Wall Connector) and TESLA_SUPERCHARGER refer to non-standardized charging ports/methods used by Tesla. GBT_AC refers to connector specified in GB/T 20234.2. GBT_DC refers to connector specified in GB/T 20234.3. Also specified as BB Configuration in IEC 62196-3. OTHER shall be used for charging ports not included in the list above. For additional information see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEC_62196.
configString: A list of the supported (i.e., available) charging inlets in a particular charging port. IEC types refer to IEC 62196,  GBT refers to  GB/T 20234.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_EVSE_ID
comment: Length of id between 7 and 37 characters. ZZ00000 to be used if SECC cannot provide id
configString: EVSE charging point ID (without separators) of last or current charging event according to ISO 15118-2 Annex H.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_IS_CHARGING
configString: True if charging is ongoing. Charging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from charger to vehicle.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_IS_DISCHARGING
configString: True if discharging (vehicle to grid) is ongoing. Discharging is considered to be ongoing if energy is flowing from vehicle to charger/grid.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_LOCATION_ALTITUDE
configString: Altitude relative to WGS 84 reference ellipsoid of last or current charging event.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_LOCATION_LATITUDE
configString: Latitude of last or current charging event in WGS 84 geodetic coordinates.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_LOCATION_LONGITUDE
configString: Longitude of last or current charging event in WGS 84 geodetic coordinates.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_MAXIMUM_CHARGING_CURRENT_DC
configString: Maximum DC charging current at inlet that can be accepted by the system.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_MAXIMUM_CHARGING_CURRENT_PHASE1
configString: Maximum AC charging current (rms) at inlet for Phase 1 that can be accepted by the system.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_MAXIMUM_CHARGING_CURRENT_PHASE2
configString: Maximum AC charging current (rms) at inlet for Phase 2 that can be accepted by the system.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_MAXIMUM_CHARGING_CURRENT_PHASE3
configString: Maximum AC charging current (rms) at inlet for Phase 3 that can be accepted by the system.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_MAX_POWER
configString: Maximum charging power of last or current charging event.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_POWER_LOSS
configString: Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside the AC/DC converter.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_START_STOP_CHARGING
configString: Start or stop the charging process.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_TEMPERATURE
configString: Current temperature of AC/DC converter converting grid voltage to battery voltage.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_TIMER_MODE
configString: Defines timer mode for charging: INACTIVE - no timer set, charging may start as soon as battery is connected to a charger. START_TIME - charging shall start at Charging.Timer.Time. END_TIME - charging shall be finished (reach Charging.ChargeLimit) at Charging.Timer.Time. When charging is completed the vehicle shall change mode to 'inactive' or set a new Charging.Timer.Time. Charging shall start immediately if mode is 'starttime' or 'endtime' and Charging.Timer.Time is a time in the past.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_TIMER_TIME
configString: Time for next charging-related action, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone. Value has no significance if Charging.Timer.Mode is 'inactive'.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CHARGING_TIME_TO_COMPLETE
comment: Shall consider time set by Charging.Timer.Time. E.g. if charging shall start in 3 hours and 2 hours of charging is needed, then Charging.TimeToComplete shall report 5 hours.
configString: The time needed for the current charging process to reach Charging.ChargeLimit. 0 if charging is complete or no charging process is active or planned.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CURRENT_CURRENT
configString: Current current flowing in/out of battery. Positive = Current flowing in to battery, e.g. during charging. Negative = Current flowing out of battery, e.g. during driving.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CURRENT_POWER
configString: Current electrical energy flowing in/out of battery. Positive = Energy flowing in to battery, e.g. during charging. Negative = Energy flowing out of battery, e.g. during driving.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_CURRENT_VOLTAGE
configString: Current Voltage of the battery.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_DCDC_POWER_LOSS
configString: Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside DC/DC converter.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_DCDC_TEMPERATURE
configString: Current temperature of DC/DC converter converting battery high voltage to vehicle low voltage (typically 12 Volts).

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_ERROR_CODES
comment: Error code format is not defined, it may be DTCs according to OBD II (SAE-J2012DA_201812) standard ([P|C|B|U]XXXXX ) or any other format.
configString: Current error codes related to the battery, if any.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_GROSS_CAPACITY
configString: Gross capacity of the battery.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_ID
comment: This could be serial number, part number plus serial number, UUID, or any other identifier that the OEM want to use to uniquely identify the battery individual.
configString: Battery Identification Number as assigned by OEM.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_IS_GROUND_CONNECTED
comment: It might be possible to disconnect the traction battery used by an electric powertrain. This is achieved by connectors, typically one for plus and one for minus.
configString: Indicating if the ground (negative terminator) of the traction battery is connected to the powertrain.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_IS_POWER_CONNECTED
comment: It might be possible to disconnect the traction battery used by an electric powertrain. This is achieved by connectors, typically one for plus and one for minus.
configString: Indicating if the power (positive terminator) of the traction battery is connected to the powertrain.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_MAX_VOLTAGE
configString: Max allowed voltage of the battery, e.g. during charging.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_NET_CAPACITY
configString: Total net capacity of the battery considering aging.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_NOMINAL_VOLTAGE
comment: Nominal voltage typically refers to voltage of fully charged battery when delivering rated capacity.
configString: Nominal Voltage of the battery.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_POWER_LOSS
configString: Electrical energy lost by power dissipation to heat inside the battery.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_PRODUCTION_DATE
configString: Production date of battery in ISO8601 format, e.g. YYYY-MM-DD.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_RANGE
configString: Remaining range in meters using only battery.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_STATE_OF_CHARGE_CURRENT
configString: Physical state of charge of the high voltage battery, relative to net capacity. This is not necessarily the state of charge being displayed to the customer.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_STATE_OF_CHARGE_CURRENT_ENERGY
comment: Current energy could be calculated as .StateOfCharge.Current * .NetCapacity.
configString: Physical state of charge of high voltage battery expressed in kWh.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_STATE_OF_CHARGE_DISPLAYED
configString: State of charge displayed to the customer.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_STATE_OF_HEALTH
comment: Exact formula is implementation dependent. Could be e.g. current capacity at 20 degrees Celsius divided with original capacity at the same temperature.
configString: Calculated battery state of health at standard conditions.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_TEMPERATURE_AVERAGE
configString: Current average temperature of the battery cells.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_TEMPERATURE_CELL_TEMPERATURE
comment: Cells are identified by relative position in array.
configString: Array of cell temperatures. Length or array shall correspond to number of cells in vehicle.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_TEMPERATURE_MAX
configString: Current maximum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the hottest cell.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_TEMPERATURE_MIN
configString: Current minimum temperature of the battery cells, i.e. temperature of the coldest cell.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRACTION_BATTERY_TIME_REMAINING
configString: Time remaining in seconds before the battery is empty.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_CLUTCH_ENGAGEMENT
configString: Clutch engagement. 0% = Clutch fully disengaged. 100% = Clutch fully engaged.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_CLUTCH_WEAR
configString: Clutch wear as a percent. 0 = no wear. 100 = worn.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_CURRENT_GEAR
configString: The current gear. 0=Neutral, 1/2/..=Forward, -1/-2/..=Reverse.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_DIFF_LOCK_FRONT_ENGAGEMENT
configString: Front Diff Lock engagement. 0% = Diff lock fully disengaged. 100% = Diff lock fully engaged.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_DIFF_LOCK_REAR_ENGAGEMENT
configString: Rear Diff Lock engagement. 0% = Diff lock fully disengaged. 100% = Diff lock fully engaged.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_DRIVE_TYPE
configString: Drive type.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_GEAR_CHANGE_MODE
configString: Is the gearbox in automatic or manual (paddle) mode.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_GEAR_COUNT
configString: Number of forward gears in the transmission. -1 = CVT.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_IS_ELECTRICAL_POWERTRAIN_ENGAGED
comment: In some hybrid solutions it is possible to disconnect/disengage the electrical powertrain mechanically to avoid induced voltage reaching a too high level when driving at high speed.
configString: Is electrical powertrain mechanically connected/engaged to the drivetrain or not. False = Disconnected/Disengaged. True = Connected/Engaged.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_IS_LOW_RANGE_ENGAGED
comment: The possibility to switch between low and high gear range is typically only available in heavy vehicles and off-road vehicles.
configString: Is gearbox in low range mode or not. False = Normal/High range engaged. True = Low range engaged.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_IS_PARK_LOCK_ENGAGED
configString: Is the transmission park lock engaged or not. False = Disengaged. True = Engaged.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_PERFORMANCE_MODE
configString: Current gearbox performance mode.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_SELECTED_GEAR
configString: The selected gear. 0=Neutral, 1/2/..=Forward, -1/-2/..=Reverse, 126=Park, 127=Drive.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_TEMPERATURE
configString: The current gearbox temperature.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_TORQUE_DISTRIBUTION
configString: Torque distribution between front and rear axle in percent. -100% = Full torque to front axle, 0% = 50:50 Front/Rear, 100% = Full torque to rear axle.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_TRAVELLED_DISTANCE
configString: Odometer reading, total distance travelled during the lifetime of the transmission.

name: POWERTRAIN_TRANSMISSION_TYPE
configString: Transmission type.

name: POWERTRAIN_TYPE
comment: For vehicles with a combustion engine (including hybrids) more detailed information on fuels supported can be found in FuelSystem.SupportedFuelTypes and FuelSystem.SupportedFuels.
configString: Defines the powertrain type of the vehicle.

name: POWER_OPTIMIZE_LEVEL
configString: Power optimization level for this branch/subsystem. A higher number indicates more aggressive power optimization. Level 0 indicates that all functionality is enabled, no power optimization enabled. Level 10 indicates most aggressive power optimization mode, only essential functionality enabled.

name: ROOF_LOAD
configString: The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

name: SERVICE_DISTANCE_TO_SERVICE
configString: Remaining distance to service (of any kind). Negative values indicate service overdue.

name: SERVICE_IS_SERVICE_DUE
configString: Indicates if vehicle needs service (of any kind). True = Service needed now or in the near future. False = No known need for service.

name: SERVICE_TIME_TO_SERVICE
configString: Remaining time to service (of any kind). Negative values indicate service overdue.

name: SPEED
configString: Vehicle speed.

name: START_TIME
comment: This signal is supposed to be set whenever a new trip starts. A new trip is considered to start when engine gets enabled (e.g. LowVoltageSystemState in ON or START mode). A trip is considered to end when engine is no longer enabled. The default value indicates that the vehicle never has been started, or that latest start time is unknown.
configString: Start time of current or latest trip, formatted according to ISO 8601 with UTC time zone.

name: TRAILER_IS_CONNECTED
configString: Signal indicating if trailer is connected or not.

name: TRAVELED_DISTANCE
configString: Odometer reading, total distance traveled during the lifetime of the vehicle.

name: TRAVELED_DISTANCE_SINCE_START
comment: A new trip is considered to start when engine gets enabled (e.g. LowVoltageSystemState in ON or START mode). A trip is considered to end when engine is no longer enabled. The signal may however keep the value of the last trip until a new trip is started.
configString: Distance traveled since start of current trip.

name: TRIP_DURATION
comment: This signal is not assumed to be continuously updated, but instead set to 0 when a trip starts and set to the actual duration of the trip when a trip ends. A new trip is considered to start when engine gets enabled (e.g. LowVoltageSystemState in ON or START mode). A trip is considered to end when engine is no longer enabled.
configString: Duration of latest trip.

name: TRIP_METER_READING
comment: The trip meter is an odometer that can be manually reset by the driver
configString: Trip meter reading.

name: TURNING_DIAMETER
configString: Minimum turning diameter, Wall-to-Wall, as defined by SAE J1100-2009 D102.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_ACRISS_CODE
configString: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_BODY_TYPE
configString: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_BRAND
configString: Vehicle brand or manufacturer.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_DATE_VEHICLE_FIRST_REGISTERED
configString: The date in ISO 8601 format of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_KNOWN_VEHICLE_DAMAGES
configString: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_LICENSE_PLATE
comment: Depending on the context, this attribute might not be up to date or might be misconfigured, and therefore should be considered untrustworthy in the absence of another method of verification.
configString: The license plate of the vehicle.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_MEETS_EMISSION_STANDARD
configString: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_MODEL
configString: Vehicle model.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_OPTIONAL_EXTRAS
comment: Allowed values are not standardized, each OEM can specify detail descriptions of array elements.
configString: Optional extras refers to all car equipment options that are not installed as standard by the manufacturer.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_PRODUCTION_DATE
configString: The date in ISO 8601 format of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_PURCHASE_DATE
configString: The date in ISO 8601 format of the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_CONFIGURATION
configString: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_EXTERIOR_COLOR
configString: The main color of the exterior within the basic color palette (eg. red, blue, black, white, ...).

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_INTERIOR_COLOR
configString: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_INTERIOR_TYPE
configString: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.).

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_MODEL_DATE
configString: The release date in ISO 8601 format of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_SEATING_CAPACITY
configString: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VEHICLE_SPECIAL_USAGE
configString: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_VIN
configString: 17-character Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) as defined by ISO 3779.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_WMI
configString: 3-character World Manufacturer Identification (WMI) as defined by ISO 3780.

name: VEHICLE_IDENTIFICATION_YEAR
configString: Model year of the vehicle.

name: VERSION_VSS_LABEL
comment: COVESA VSS project typically use dev for latest master, and empty string for released versions.
configString: Label to further describe the version.

name: VERSION_VSS_MAJOR
configString: Supported Version of VSS - Major version.

name: VERSION_VSS_MINOR
configString: Supported Version of VSS - Minor version.

name: VERSION_VSS_PATCH
configString: Supported Version of VSS - Patch version.

name: WIDTH_EXCLUDING_MIRRORS
configString: Overall vehicle width excluding mirrors, as defined by SAE J1100-2009 W103.

name: WIDTH_FOLDED_MIRRORS
configString: Overall vehicle width with mirrors folded, as defined by SAE J1100-2009 W145.

name: WIDTH_INCLUDING_MIRRORS
configString: Overall vehicle width including mirrors, as defined by SAE J1100-2009 W144.
